         Job Description
          Job Title: Data Analytics Scientist
          Position Overview/Description:
         Ford Motor Company's Global Data Insight & Analytics (GDIA) organization is looking for an analytics scientistthat has a deep understanding of data management and analysis. You will have the opportunity to work with some ofthe brightest global subject matter experts that are transforming the automobile industry. In this role, you will support the development of optimization models by assembling data from a variety of sources as a member of the Advanced Operational Analytics team in GDIA. The developed models will provide decision support to other Ford organizations, such as Product Development, Strategy, and Sustainability. Additionally, you will support initiatives to leverage unique data streams using predictive analytics, and quantify the customer value of vehicle technologies.
          Responsibilities:
         You will be responsible for providing the data analytics support for departmental tasks, including assembly of data for building models and performing predictive/prescriptive analytics. In addition, you will:
           Ingest large data sets from a variety of sources (SQL, Teradata, Oracle, Hadoop, and 3
            rd
           party sources in the public domain)
           Support analytical model building by data mapping and preprocessing, and document information flows
           Identify key data elements to extract/decode/analyze
           Develop predictive analytics and machine learning algorithms using business critical datasets
           Work collaboratively with various business groups and regionsto disseminate critical information and develop strategic opportunities
          Job Requirements:
          Basic Qualifications:
           Master of Science Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, Management Information Systems or Physics
           2+ years of academic or business experience in one or more of the following:
             A data analytics role including running queries and compiling data
             Predictive analytics including machine learning
             Big Data technologies including Greenplum, Python, or Hadoop (HDFS, MapReduce, Hive, Shark, Spark, etc.), command line experience with loading and manipulating files within HDFS
          Preferred Qualifications:
           PhD in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, Management Information Systems or Physics
           Knowledge of data transfer and ingestion technologies including Talend and HVR
           Demonstrated experience building visualizations using Tableau/Qlikview/Alteryx
           Expertise with manipulating data to form unified data sets for analysis
           Ability to write complex NoSQL queries needed to identify & analyze data
           Experience with SPSS, AMPL, WEKA, Matlab, R, SAS, or similar software
           Strong oral, written, and interpersonal communication skills
           Proficiency in Word, Excel and PowerPoint
           Experience working with global teams
           Comfortable working in an environment where problems are not always well-defined, and interested in learning new tools and techniques
         The distance between imagination and … creation. It can be measured in years of innovation, or in moments of brilliance. When you join the Ford team; discover all the benefits, rewards and development opportunities you’d expect from a diverse global leader. You’ll become part of a team that is already leading the way, with ingenious solutions and attainable products – and it is always ready to go further.
